<section class="calc-content">
  <h2>How the Math Works</h2>
  <h3>Solar Array Sizing</h3>
  <p>Array size (watts) = (Daily Wh × 1.25 inefficiency factor) / Peak Sun Hours. The 25% inefficiency factor accounts for inverter losses, wiring resistance, panel degradation, and non-optimal angles.</p>
  
  <h3>Battery Bank Sizing</h3>
  <p>Battery capacity (Wh) = (Daily Wh × Days of Autonomy) / Depth of Discharge. We use 80% DoD for LFP (LiFePO₄) batteries — the safest balance between usable capacity and cycle life.</p>
  
  <h3>Wind Supplement</h3>
  <p>Turbine power follows the cubic wind law: P = 0.5 × ρ × A × v³ × C<sub>p</sub>. At wind speeds below 4 m/s (~9 mph), small turbines generate negligible power. Above 5 m/s, they become viable supplements.</p>

